question: You are using nmap to perform a SYN scan (a TCP half open scan.) The target machine is not listening on any of the ports you scan. When the target machine responds back, which of the following TCP flags do you expect to see in the packets you receive?
feedback: The TCP RST flag indicates that connection should be immediately terminated, and this happens mostly because of a fatal error.
